cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.PF, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the behavior of IEEE 802.11 protocol, which is a wireless networking standard. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper deals with the estimation of packet delay distribution, which is related to information theory. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper proposes a model for estimating packet delay distribution, which can be seen as a control system. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is a relevant category as the paper addresses the challenge of ensuring quality of service in wireless networks, which is related to performance. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper mentions packet loss rate, which can affect multimedia applications.
